Write a changelog entry for this change:

{{change}}

Write it for users, not maintainers: what changed from their perspective, why it matters, and any action they must take. Categorize it (Added/Changed/Fixed/Deprecated/Removed/Security). For breaking changes, lead with the migration step. Keep it to a couple of crisp lines.

Write release notes for version {{version}} from these changes:

{{changes}}

Lead with what users gain and what they must do. Group by Highlights, Changes, Fixes, and Breaking. For breaking changes, give the exact migration step up front. Write for users, not maintainers: skip internal refactors with no user-visible effect. Keep it skimmable and honest about known issues.
